# FYP Documentation — UniSchedule AI

## Key files

| Path | Purpose |
|------|---------|
| `docs/PROJECT-NOTES.md` | Living plan — update Section 13 after supervisor meetings |
| `docs/supervisor-submission/` | Week 3 pack (research, design, evaluation) |

## Writing standards

- **Harvard** referencing in literature and dissertation text
- Tie features to **RQ1–RQ5** and evaluation metrics
- Distinguish Must / Should / Won't (MoSCoW) when proposing features

## Supervisor expectations

- Research gap, methodology, primary data (survey/interviews), evaluation plan
- Diagrams: architecture, ER, use cases, scheduling flow, AI decision flow
- Security: Sanctum, RBAC, privacy — see `06-evaluation-security-ethics.md`

## When editing submission docs

- Replace placeholders: `[Your Full Name]`, `[Student ID]`, `[Date]`
- Do not claim completed work (survey live, code working) unless true
- Export to PDF via Word for professional formatting (no broken markdown `---` in PDF)

## Tech stack in docs

Next.js, Laravel, MySQL, Laravel Sanctum — keep consistent across all documents.
